quote.text: Nobody talked about our front seven.
quote.author: Mike Macdonald

stories.headline: DEFENSE REIGNS SUPREME
stories.subhead: Seahawks dismantle Patriots 29-13...
stories.body: The dynasty talk was premature...

stories.headline: Drake Maye Powers Seattle Seahawks Win
stories.subhead: Final • NFL
stories.body:
In NFL action, Seattle Seahawks defeated New England Patriots 13-29. Leading the way was Drake Maye, who recorded 27/43, 295 YDS, 2 TD, 2 INT (Passing Leader). Their impact was felt on nearly every possession. The victory was a testament to execution down the stretch.

This result has implications for the season standings. Seattle Seahawks demonstrated why they are a tough matchup, controlling the tempo and forcing New England Patriots into uncomfortable situations.

"We just tried to execute the game plan," said a team representative post-game. "Getting the win against a quality opponent like New England Patriots builds confidence for the group."

game_data.game_note: Seattle Seahawks at New England Patriots Super Bowl LX
